description: thing +‎ -like. Compare English thingly, German dinglich.

adjectives.description: thinglike (comparative more thinglike, superlative most thinglike)

entries.meaning: (philosophy) Resembling a thing; having the properties associated with a physical object; objectlike.
examples: Although Tex had assured me only the other day that New Yorkers prized intelligence, I wasn’t sure mine could be counted on. It didn’t feel like a thing in our very thinglike world, a world where identity began with the choice of massive automobile  […]
